1. Z0 {Today, the theory of the queenside majority has changed very little, but its relative importance has declined. Modern openings abound in which one side or the other voluntarily accepts a queenside majority; such minorities may even constitute an advantage as late as the early stages of the endgame. Another serious consideration is that acquiring a queenside majority usually tends to mean ceding a central majority. For one thing, we have just seen positions in which a minority is more effective than a majority. Furthermore, we must keep in mind that the advance of a majority will/might often simply expose weaknesses behind the very same pawns that have advanced. Examine all cases with care…} *

