1. Z0 {There do exist some openings where one side is early ceding a 'healthy' pawn majority to his opponent, seeking other compensating elements. One bare element is not enough to correctly evaluate a position; a chess player should take into account the total situation of the board. More or less, both sides have their pros and cons, and it is really looking too early for a definitive evaluation… In the next four games, we will examine exactly these 'healthy' majorities which constitute of one-side majority, as the other side simply does not have a majority at all! This happens due to the appearance of early doubled pawns and it seems to be a quite sensitive concept.} *

