8. Qf4 {[%mdl 32768] Relying on his better pawn structure, White aims for the endgame.} Be6 {[%csl Rc3,Gc5,Ge6,Ge7] Black must play as energetically as possible. In the Scotch, White invests time (moving the king's knight twice) to gain a structural advantage. White has the better pawn structure but in return, Black has a lead in development.} ({The previous try was} 8... Ng6 9. Qxf6 gxf6 {, but it seems that the text move appears to be rather good. White anyway will be forced to exchange queens and Black will get even quicker development than in case of 8...Ng6.}) 9. Qxf6 gxf6 {[%csl Rc3,Gc5,Rc6,Rc7,Ge6,Ge7,Rf6,Rf7][%cal Gf6f5] It seems that Black has gone astray; he did not only double his queenside pawns but he also ruined his kingside pawns too! But in reality, he will soon play ...f5.} *

