16. Bb4 {[%csl Re7,Rf5][%mdl 32768] e7 and f5 are hanging. How do you solve this concrete problem?} Rxd1+ $1 17. Rxd1 (17. Kxd1 hxg3 18. hxg3 Kd8 {is also OK.} 19. Bxe7+ $6 {White shouldn't give up the bishop pair unless there is an immediate benefit.} Kxe7 20. exf5 $2 Bd5 $17 21. Rf1 Bxg3 {Black regains the pawn, has the bishop pair and far superior pawn structure.}) 17... hxg3 18. hxg3 (18. Bxe7 $2 gxh2) 18... b5 {[%cal Gc8b7] Resourceful aggression. The e7-knight still couldn't move because f5 was attacked. ...b5 also creates an escape square for the king.} (18... Rxg3 $4 19. Bxe7 Rxh3 20. Rd8#) 19. Bxe7 bxa4 20. Bxf5 ({It was important to notice in advance that after} 20. exf5 {, Black has} Bxa2 {.}) 20... Bxf5 21. exf5 Be3+ {White's king is forced into the corner.} 22. Kb1 Rxg3 {Black is not in danger of losing anymore.} *

