44... Ba7 {[%mdl 32768] Find the final part of the winning concept.} 45. g5 $1 {Obviously, the plan with h4, Be7, Kxg6 and pushing the h-pawn is not available now.} Bb6 46. Bg1 Ba7 47. f5 $1 {An instructive pawn break.} exf5 48. e6+ Kxe6 49. Kxg6 Z0 ({Black's bishop must immediately come to e5 to stop the g-pawn, giving up the c5-pawn, so White didn't even sacrifice a pawn. Next, Black's passed f-pawn is far inferior to White's g-pawn, and White easily wins, for example:} 49... Bb8 50. Kh7 Be5 51. g6 f4 52. g7 Bxg7 53. Kxg7 f3 54. Kf8 Ke5 55. Ke7 Ke4 56. Kd6 Kd3 57. Kxc6 Kc2 58. Kxc5 Kb2 59. Kxb4 {.}) *

