1. d4 {[%mdl 32768]} d5 2. c4 dxc4 3. Nf3 Nf6 4. e3 Bg4 5. Bxc4 e6 6. h3 Bh5 7. Nc3 Nbd7 8. O-O Bd6 9. e4 e5 10. Be2 O-O 11. Bg5 Bxf3 12. Bxf3 exd4 13. Qxd4 h6 14. Bh4 Ne5 15. Rad1 {White's pieces are exerting unpleasant pressure on the opponent's position. Black chooses a forcing variation, involving a transition into an endgame.} g5 $5 ({The text looks better than} 15... Re8 16. Be2 Ng6 17. Bxf6 Qxf6 18. Qxf6 gxf6 $14 {Darga-Matulovic, Siegen 1970.}) 16. Bg3 Nxf3+ $2 ({Although the text looks 'nice', Black should have opted for} 16... Qe7 17. Be2 Rfd8 18. Nd5 Nxd5 19. exd5 $14 {.}) 17. gxf3 Bxg3 18. fxg3 Qxd4+ 19. Rxd4 Rfd8 20. Rfd1 Rxd4 21. Rxd4 {Despite the numerous exchanges, Black's position remains difficult. White's kingside majority looks dangerous and quite mobile. Also, the black h-pawn looks rather weak.} Re8 ({Passive defense by} 21... Kf8 22. Kf2 {22.Nb5 c6 23.Nd6 Rd8 24.Nf5 Rxd4 25.Nxd4 h5 $14} Ke7 23. Nd1 $1 c5 24. Rd3 Rd8 25. Rxd8 Kxd8 26. Ne3 h5 27. Nf5 Ne8 28. h4 gxh4 29. gxh4 $16 {doesn't fully solve Black's problems.}) 22. Kf2 Re6 23. f4 Rb6 24. Rd2 gxf4 25. gxf4 Rb4 26. Ke3 Kf8 27. b3 $1 {White is not in a hurry to take positive action and first strengthens his position.} c6 28. Rd8+ $6 {This invasion by the white rook looks attractive.} (28. e5 $6 {, would have afforded Black additional counter chances after} Nh5 {.}) ({It has to be noted that} 28. Rd6 $1 {was stronger:} Ke7 {28...Kg7 29.e5 Ne8 30.Rd8 Kf8 31.Ne4 Ke7 32.Rb8+-} 29. e5 Nh5 30. Ne4 {.}) 28... Ke7 29. Rh8 a5 $6 (29... h5 $1 {was more stubborn:} 30. Kd3 {30.e5?! Nd5+ 31.Nxd5+ cxd5 32.Rxh5 a5= $13} a6 31. Ke3 a5 32. Ra8 b6 33. Ra7+ Ke8 $16 {.}) 30. Rxh6 a4 31. bxa4 Nd7 32. Rh5 $6 ({Preventing ...Nc5. But good was} 32. a5 Nc5 33. e5 Rc4 34. Ne2 {.}) 32... Nb6 $2 {Loses.} ({Black had to be active by} 32... Rb2 $1 33. Rh8 Rc2 34. Kd3 Rf2 35. Ne2 Rf3+ 36. Kd4 Nf8 37. Kc4 $16 {.}) 33. a5 Na4 34. Ne2 (34. Nxa4 Rxa4 35. Kf3 Rxa2 36. h4 {was natural and good.}) 34... Rb2 35. Nd4 Rxa2 36. Nf5+ Kd7 37. Rh7 Ke6 38. Rh6+ Kd7 ({If} 38... f6 $6 {, then} 39. Rh7 $1 {mates.}) 39. Rf6 Ra3+ 40. Kd4 Nb2 41. Rxf7+ 1-0

