1. d4 {[%mdl 32768]} Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nf3 Bb4+ 4. Bd2 Bxd2+ 5. Qxd2 O-O 6. g3 d5 7. Bg2 Nbd7 8. O-O c6 9. Rc1 Qe7 10. Qe3 Re8 11. Nbd2 e5 12. dxe5 Nxe5 13. Qxe5 Qxe5 14. Nxe5 Rxe5 15. cxd5 Nxd5 16. e4 Nb6 17. f4 Re7 18. a4 a5 {(D) StartSquare#EndSquare White has a slight advantage thanks to the fact that his central/kingside pawn majority is more active than Black's on the queenside, his better central control, the better bishop and the possibility of his knight pressurising the black queenside from c5.} 19. Nb3 $1 f6 20. Ra3 $1 {The white rook prepares to apply pressure on the queenside by its transfer to b3.} (20. Nc5 {, would have been premature due to} Nd7 $1 {.}) 20... Be6 21. Nc5 $1 Bf7 {Compulsory, as after} (21... Rd8 22. Nxe6 Rxe6 23. Rb3 {, Black's position collapses.}) 22. Rd3 Rae8 23. Bh3 Nc8 ({Black could not play} 23... Bg6 24. Rb3 Nxa4 25. Nxa4 Rxe4 26. Nc5 Re1+ 27. Rxe1 Rxe1+ 28. Kf2 Rh1 29. Be6+ {,}) ({but} 23... g6 24. Rd4 f5 $5 {was interesting.}) 24. Bd7 Rd8 25. Rcd1 {By attacking the b-pawn, White forces the black knight to return to its post.} Nb6 26. Bg4 Rxd3 27. Rxd3 Kf8 28. Rd8+ Re8 29. Rd4 $1 {Now the threat of 30.b4! is truly dangerous and Black can meet it in only one way.} Rb8 30. Rd7 $1 {With the help of tactical devices White transforms his positional superiority into material gain.} h5 31. Bh3 Ke8 32. Rc7 Na8 33. Rxb7 Rxb7 34. Nxb7 Nb6 35. Nd6+ $1 ({White could also win with} 35. Nc5 Ke7 36. b3 $1 Kd6 37. Nb7+ Kc7 38. Nxa5 Nxa4 39. bxa4 Kb6 40. Nxc6 {.}) 35... Ke7 36. Nxf7 Nxa4 $5 ({Played in an effort to complicate the position, as} 36... Kxf7 37. b3 {would not leave Black any hope.}) 37. Nh8 $1 Nxb2 38. e5 a4 39. Ng6+ Ke8 ({Nothing would change after} 39... Kf7 40. e6+ Ke8 {40...Kxg6 41.f5+} 41. Bg2 {.}) 40. Be6 Nd3 41. Bg8 $1 {With the idea of 42.e6, 43.Bf7+ and 44.e7+.} fxe5 ({No salvation is offered by} 41... Nb4 42. e6 Nd5 43. Bf7+ Kd8 44. e7+ Nxe7 45. Nxe7 Kxe7 46. Ba2 {.}) 42. Nxe5 Nb4 43. Nc4 h4 44. Bh7 hxg3 45. hxg3 Ke7 46. Be4 Kf6 47. g4 Ke6 48. Kf2 Nd5 49. Kf3 Nb4 50. g5 c5 51. f5+ Ke7 52. Ke3 Kf8 53. Kd2 Ke7 54. Kc3 1-0

