1. d4 {[%mdl 32768]} Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nf3 b6 4. g3 Bb7 5. Bg2 Bb4+ 6. Bd2 Be7 7. Nc3 O-O 8. O-O c5 9. d5 exd5 10. Nh4 Ne4 11. Nf5 Bf6 12. cxd5 Nxc3 13. Bxc3 Bxc3 14. bxc3 Qf6 15. e4 d6 16. Qd2 Bc8 17. Ne3 Nd7 18. f4 Ba6 19. Rfe1 Rae8 20. Ng4 Qd8 21. Re3 Bc8 22. Nf2 b5 23. Rae1 f6 24. Bf1 Qa5 25. Qe2 c4 26. Bh3 Nb6 27. Bxc8 Rxc8 28. Qd2 Rc5 {White should feel happy due to his more centralised pieces and his mobile central pawn majority. But it is essential to force the e5 advance, activating his rooks and to activate his knight as well. The not so good placed knight should be transferred to a better square, namely c6 or e6.} 29. g4 $1 {Preparing the knight-route to d4-square via h1.} Qa6 $6 {Black loses valuable time. He should also think of improving his knight and this is better done to the c5-square.} ({So,} 29... Nd7 $1 {, was a must:} 30. Nh1 Rc7 31. Ng3 Nc5 32. Nf5 Nd3 33. Rf1 $13 {. He obviously thought that his knight on b6 defends against the e5-advance, because of the pressure on the d5-pawn.}) 30. Nh1 $1 Qc8 31. h3 Re8 $6 ({Although Black lost time with his queen, he should again opt for placing his knight on c5:} 31... Rc7 32. Ng3 Nd7 33. Nf5 Qa6 34. Ne7+ Kh8 35. Nc6 $14 {.}) 32. Ng3 g6 33. Ne2 Qd7 34. Nd4 {Now Black is in trouble - the white knight makes the difference...} Rcc8 35. Rd1 $2 ({Here White could play} 35. f5 $1 {. After} g5 {35...a6 36.fxg6 hxg6 37.Rf1 Qe7 38.Ne6 $16} 36. Ne6 {, and ideas as Qd4 and h4-Rh3, he would have a nearly decisive advantage.}) 35... Na4 $1 36. Nc6 $6 ({Again} 36. f5 $1 Nc5 37. Ne6 {, would be preferable. But White was focused on the e5-advance...}) 36... a6 37. Qd4 Rf8 {Now everything has been prepared for the final assault, something quite common in modern players’ games; something that it is driven by the ‘plan’!} 38. e5 $1 {The central pawn majority is advancing with great effect!} fxe5 39. fxe5 dxe5 $2 {The decisive mistake.} ({Black should have opted for} 39... Rce8 $1 40. e6 Qg7 $16 {.}) 40. Rxe5 $2 ({After} 40. Nxe5 $1 Qd6 41. g5 $1 {, the threat Ng4 is difficult to meet...}) 40... Rxc6 $2 ({Panic! Black had to try to defend with} 40... Rce8 41. Rde1 Rxe5 42. Qxe5 $16 {.}) 41. dxc6 Qxc6 42. Re7 Qf6 43. Qxf6 Rxf6 44. Rd8+ Rf8 45. Rdd7 1-0

