{I was lucky to watch the 2nd example live, as I was present in 2013 Tata Steel:} 1. d4 {[%mdl 32768]} Nf6 2. c4 c5 3. d5 e6 4. Nc3 exd5 5. cxd5 d6 6. g3 g6 7. Bg2 Bg7 8. Nf3 O-O 9. O-O Re8 10. Nd2 b6 11. a4 Nbd7 12. h3 a6 13. Rb1 Qe7 14. Nc4 Ne5 15. Nxb6 Rb8 16. Nxc8 Rexc8 17. b3 Nh5 18. Bd2 Rc7 19. Qc2 Rcb7 20. Rfc1 f5 21. e3 Nf6 22. Ne2 Ne4 23. Bxe4 fxe4 24. Qxe4 Rxb3 25. Rxb3 Rxb3 26. Bc3 Qd7 27. f4 Nf7 28. g4 Bxc3 29. Nxc3 Qd8 30. Qc2 Qb6 31. Qd2 {Black's knight looks more or less OK, but still, it lacks any good attacking square. And passivity is not welcomed by the new generation!} g5 $5 ({After} 31... Kg7 32. g5 $1 h6 33. h4 Qb4 34. Rc2 {, chances would be more or less equal.}) 32. Rc2 $6 ({The active} 32. Ne4 $1 {should be best:} Qb4 {32...gxf4 33.exf4 Qb4 34.Nf6+ Kg7 35.Nh5+ Kf8 36.Qxb4 Rxb4 37.a5 $14} 33. Qxb4 Rxb4 34. Nxg5 Nxg5 35. fxg5 Rxa4 36. Rb1 Ra2 $1 {36...Rb4?! 37.Ra1 Rb6 38.Kf2 $16} 37. Rb6 a5 38. Rxd6 a4 39. Rd8+ Kf7 40. Rd7+ Kg6 41. d6 Rd2 42. Ra7 Kxg5 43. d7 h5 44. gxh5 Kxh5 45. Kf1 a3 46. Ke1 Rd6 {. Note that if White wants to have a passed & protected pawn with f5, then he would have to live with an excellent placed black knight on e5.}) 32... Qb4 $1 {Now Black improves his queen before any further operation.} 33. Kh2 Qc4 34. Kg2 Nh8 $1 {The knight tour begins...} 35. Kf2 Ng6 36. Ne2 ({White could think of} 36. fxg5 Ne5 $13 {.}) 36... Qxa4 37. Rb2 $6 ({White's time-trouble was a key factor here, as he missed his chances with} 37. Ra2 Qc4 38. Qa5 $1 {38.fxg5 Ne5 39.Nf4 Qe4 $17} Qxd5 39. Qd8+ Kf7 40. Qxg5 Qxg5 41. fxg5 Rb6 42. Nf4 $13 {.}) 37... gxf4 38. exf4 $2 {Another grave mistake.} ({Forced was} 38. Rxb3 Qxb3 39. exf4 Qxh3 40. Qb2 $1 Qh4+ {40...Qxg4 41.Qb8+ Kf7 42.Qxd6 $13} 41. Ke3 Qe7+ 42. Kf3 a5 $15 {.}) 38... c4 $2 {Returning the favour.} (38... Rxh3 $1 39. Rb8+ Kf7 40. Rb7+ Ne7 {was rather easy...}) 39. f5 $2 {Ping-pong of time-trouble mistakes.} (39. Rxb3 $1 {seems to hold:} cxb3 40. f5 $1 Ne5 41. Qg5+ Kf7 42. Qh5+ {.}) 39... c3 $1 {Decisive - Black wins the white knight!} 40. Nxc3 (40. Qe3 cxb2 41. Qe6+ Kg7 42. fxg6 Rb7 {.}) 40... Qf4+ 41. Ke1 (41. Qxf4 Rxb2+ 42. Kg3 Nxf4 43. Kxf4 a5 {.}) 41... Qg3+ 42. Kd1 Rxc3 43. Rb8+ (43. fxg6 Qf3+ 44. Qe2 Qh1+ 45. Qe1 Rc1+ {.}) 43... Kg7 44. Rb7+ Kf6 45. fxg6 Qf3+ 46. Qe2 Qh1+ {White resigned due to 47.Qe1 Qxd5+ 48.Qd2 Qh1+ 49.Qe1 Rd3+ 50.Kc2 Qxe1 51.Kxd3 Qf1+ 52.Kd4 Qf2+ 53.Kc3 Qf3+ .} 0-1

