1. Z0 {Contrary to the previous chapter, here the central/kingside pawn majority is not, or it cannot be mobile. On the other hand, the opponent’s queenside (or flank in general) pawn majority becomes a major threat and can easily pose inventible problems. An endgame is (nearly) always welcomed, as the power of an outside passed pawn (which can be created by a majority) seals the game. Note that it can be central/queenside vs. kingside pawn majority as well, but for the sake of economy we use the most met in practice cases.} *

