1. d4 {[%mdl 32768]} Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nf3 b6 4. g3 Bb7 5. Bg2 Be7 6. O-O O-O 7. Nc3 Ne4 8. Qc2 Nxc3 9. Qxc3 f5 10. b3 Bf6 11. Bb2 Nc6 12. Rad1 Ne7 13. Ne1 Bxg2 14. Nxg2 g5 15. Qc2 Ng6 16. e4 f4 17. e5 Bg7 18. Qe4 Qe7 19. Rd3 Rad8 20. Re1 d5 21. exd6 Qxd6 22. Red1 Qe7 23. Ne1 Qf6 24. R1d2 {A more or less level position.} Qf5 $1 {Black's strategy is impressive and would make A.Nimzowitsch really proud in terms of minorities, majorities and blockading!} 25. Qxf5 $6 ({Looks natural, but in fact it is a mistaken approach. White should preserve the balance with} 25. Re2 {.}) 25... exf5 $1 {That's the trick - Black's kingside majority will prove more dangerous than White's one.} 26. Ng2 g4 $1 27. Nxf4 Nxf4 28. gxf4 Bh6 29. Re2 Bxf4 {Now Black has a healthier pawn structure, but White should hold. Well, easier than done, as this demands precise play and eventually excellent defensive skills, while Black is risking nearly nothing…} 30. Re6 $6 ({The text is not really helpful. A better try is} 30. Bc3 Rde8 31. Rxe8 Rxe8 32. Bd2 Bxd2 33. Rxd2 Kf7 $15) ({Or} 30. Rd1 Rfe8 31. Rde1 Kf7 $15 {.}) 30... Rfe8 $1 31. Rf6 Re1+ 32. Kg2 Rf8 $1 {Active pieces must be exchanged!} 33. Rxf8+ (33. Rc6 Re2 34. Bc3 Rxa2 $17 {.}) 33... Kxf8 34. d5 {This 'kills' White's pawn majority - the a2-b3-c4-d5 chain cannot move further anymore.} Bd6 (34... Re2 35. Ba3+ Ke8 36. d6 c5 $17 {, could have been played as well.}) 35. Bc3 (35. Re3 Rxe3 36. fxe3 Kf7 {, looks already bad for White...}) 35... Rc1 36. Bd2 Rc2 37. a4 f4 {The black kingside pawn majority is rather mobile - White is in trouble.} 38. h3 f3+ 39. Kf1 h5 40. hxg4 hxg4 {Here the game was adjourned and White sealed the move.} 41. Ke1 (41. Ke1 {And seeing that he is easily lost after} Bc5 {(zugzwang!)} 42. b4 Bd6 {, he resigned.}) ({Another move could have been} 41. Rd4 Rb2 42. Be1 Rxb3 43. Rxg4 {, when Black can pin the white bishop with} Rb1 44. Re4 Bb4 45. Re6 {And then proceed with his king:} Kf7 46. Re3 Kg6 47. Re6+ Kf5 48. Re3 {, liquidating to a won pawn ending:} Rxe1+ 49. Rxe1 Bxe1 50. Kxe1 Ke4 {.}) 0-1

