1. e4 {[%mdl 32768]} c6 2. d4 d5 3. e5 Bf5 4. c4 dxc4 5. Bxc4 e6 6. Nc3 Nd7 7. Nge2 Nb6 8. Bb3 Ne7 9. O-O Qd7 10. Nf4 h6 11. Be3 Bh7 12. Rc1 Ned5 13. Ncxd5 Nxd5 14. Nxd5 exd5 {The pawn structures have been clarified, and White has chances to exploit his majority on the kingside by pushing f4-f5.} 15. Bd2 $5 Be7 16. Rc3 Bf5 {This is the beginning of a sophisticated blockading plan with ...h5.} (16... O-O {, was simpler, when after} 17. Rg3 Kh8 18. Bc2 Bxc2 19. Qxc2 Qe6 20. f4 {, Black can blockade the vital f5-square:} f5 21. Rb3 b6 22. Bb4 Bxb4 23. Rxb4 $14 {.}) 17. Bc2 h5 $6 {The continuation of the wrong plan.} ({Even here} 17... O-O {was required:} 18. Bxf5 Qxf5 19. Re1 $14 {.}) 18. Bxf5 Qxf5 19. Qb3 Qd7 (19... Qc8 20. f4 $16 {was not advisable,}) ({but maybe Black should have given consideration to} 19... O-O-O {, even if it looks risky in view of} 20. Rfc1 {, when White has good attacking chances down the c-file.}) 20. f4 f5 ({White's f5 could not be allowed:} 20... h4 21. f5 O-O-O 22. Qd1 Bb4 23. Rh3 Bxd2 24. Qxd2 $16 {.}) 21. Rg3 (21. e6 $5 {was also promising:} Qc8 {21...Qxe6? 22.Re3+- , or 21...Qc7?! 22.Qxd5+-} 22. Re1 Bf6 23. Rd3 O-O 24. Qd1 $16 {.}) 21... Kf7 22. Bb4 {The exchange of the darksquared bishops is important for White.} Bxb4 ({Therefore} 22... Bd8 $16 {, deserved attention.}) 23. Qxb4 Rae8 {The strongly defended e5-pawn secures White a space advantage. Now his plan should be to provoke more weaknesses with his active rooks.} 24. Rff3 Re6 25. Rg5 g6 26. Ra3 b6 $6 ({Black should have avoided any further weaknesses in his pawn structure, therefore again} 26... Ra8 $16 {was safer.}) 27. h3 {White is now preparing a future g4, after of course some preparation, in order to open lines for his attacking rooks.} h4 {Black certainly wants to avoid it!} 28. Kh2 Qe7 29. Qa4 a5 30. Rb3 Qc7 31. Rc3 Rc8 32. Qc2 Qe7 $6 {A blunder.} ({Black had to play} 32... Kf8 {, when after} 33. a3 Ra8 34. b3 $16 {, White would have still to work hard for his bread.}) 33. g4 $1 hxg3+ (33... fxg4 34. Rxg4 Qf8 35. f5 {.}) 34. Rcxg3 Rh8 (34... Rg8 {also loses by} 35. Rxf5+ $1 {.}) 35. Rxg6 $1 {And Black's defensive wall is broken down.} Rxg6 36. Qxf5+ Rf6 37. exf6 Qxf6 38. Qd7+ Kf8 39. Qc8+ Kf7 40. Qc7+ Kf8 41. Rg5 $1 Rh4 42. Qc8+ Ke7 43. Rf5 Qxd4 44. Qc7+ Ke6 45. Re5+ 1-0

