{Destroying the opponent’s future majority activity is already a good sign. Blockading a majority can be also a starting point of success, as then the active play and plans of the opponent are limited. Well, nothing new under the sun; the older masters knew exactly what and how to do it! In the first example we will meet a well-known mechanism; the one of blocking the passed pawn. That’s the beauty of chess; strategical elements are mixed or either are exchanged in-between them…} 1. Z0 *

