{Black exerts pressure on a3. What should White play?} 27. Rxb7 $1 {[%mdl 32768] A nice exchange sacrifice, which gives White the upper hand.} Rxb7 28. Nxd5 (28. Bxd5 $6 Rb3 $1 {Forcing exchanges.} 29. Bxe6 Qxe6 30. d5 Qf5 $1 {gives Black active counterplay with threats like ...Qc2 or ...Rb1 if the c3-knight moves.}) 28... Qxa3 29. Nxe7+ Qxe7 30. Nc6 $14 {[%csl Gc6,Ra6,Rc4]} Z0 ({White is playing for a win without much risk. For example, after} 30... Qe8 31. Re1 Rdb8 32. Be4 Qd7 33. Qxc4 {, White has one pawn in return for the exchange and the knight on c6 is very powerful. Black will most likely lose the a6-pawn as well.}) *

