{Given Black's readiness to utilize their queenside majority and White's temporarily static kingside pawns, what move should White make to immobilize Black's majority and gain a strategic advantage in the position?} 27. a4 $1 {[%mdl 32768] A great move which suddenly immobilises this majority and, in a way, turns the tables.} *

