1. d4 {[%mdl 32768]} Nf6 2. c4 g6 3. Nc3 d5 4. cxd5 Nxd5 5. e4 Nxc3 6. bxc3 Bg7 7. Be3 c5 8. Qd2 cxd4 9. cxd4 Nc6 10. Rd1 Qa5 11. Qxa5 Nxa5 12. Bd3 O-O 13. Ne2 Bd7 14. Rb1 b6 15. Kd2 Rfc8 16. Ba6 Rd8 17. Rhc1 Bc8 18. Bd3 Bb7 19. Rc7 Rac8 20. Rbc1 Rxc7 21. Rxc7 Rc8 22. Rxc8+ Bxc8 23. Nc3 Nc6 24. Nb5 Ba6 25. Kc3 Kf8 26. a4 Bb7 {White centralised king and pieces gives him some advantage, while the black queenside majority is not looking dangerous.} 27. g4 $1 {Gaining more space is always a good strategy!} Ke8 28. Bc4 Nb8 $6 ({Black had to opt for} 28... Bc8 29. h3 Bd7 30. f4 $14 {.}) 29. Kd3 $6 (29. Nxa7 $1 {was perfectly played:} Bxe4 30. Bb5+ Kd8 31. Bf4 e5 32. dxe5 Nd7 33. g5 $16 {.}) 29... a6 30. Nc7+ Kd8 31. Nd5 Nd7 32. Nb4 a5 33. Bd5 $2 {Although it looks perfectly good, the text is failing to some nice tactics.} (33. Na2 $14 {was fine.}) 33... Bxd5 $2 ({Which Black missed! After} 33... e5 $1 34. Bxb7 exd4 35. Bxd4 Bxd4 36. Kxd4 axb4 37. Bd5 Nc5 38. a5 b3 39. axb6 b2 40. Ba2 Na4 {, Black would have nothing to afraid of.}) 34. Nxd5 e6 35. Nc3 {As now the black queenside majority is totally blocked, White enjoys an extra central pawn.} Kc7 36. Nb5+ Kc6 37. Kc4 $6 (37. g5 Bf8 38. Kc4 {was accurate and easy.}) 37... Bf8 $6 ({Black's last chance was to be found in} 37... Nf6 38. f3 Bf8 39. g5 Ne8 40. Bf4 $16 {.}) 38. Bf4 Bb4 39. f3 Bf8 40. d5+ $1 {The passed pawn will carry the day...} exd5+ 41. exd5+ Kb7 42. Nd6+ $1 Bxd6 43. Bxd6 {A good passed pawn and a better minor piece - Black's fate is sealed.} g5 44. Bg3 Nf6 ({Or} 44... Ka6 45. d6 h6 {45...Kb7 46.Kb5 Nf6 47.Be5 Nd7 48.Bd4+-} 46. Bf2 Ne5+ 47. Kd5 {.}) 45. Be5 Nd7 46. Bd4 Kc7 47. Kb5 f6 ({No chance either in} 47... Kd6 48. Bxb6 Nxb6 49. Kxb6 Kxd5 50. Kxa5 Kc5 51. Ka6 Kc6 52. a5 f6 53. Ka7 Kc7 54. a6 h6 55. h3 {.}) 48. Bf2 Kd6 49. Bxb6 Ne5 50. Bxa5 Nxf3 51. Bc3 1-0

