1. Nf3 {[%mdl 32768]} d5 2. d4 Nf6 3. c4 e6 4. Nc3 Be7 5. Bg5 h6 6. Bh4 O-O 7. e3 Ne4 8. Bxe7 Qxe7 9. cxd5 Nxc3 10. bxc3 exd5 11. Qb3 Rd8 12. c4 dxc4 13. Bxc4 Nc6 14. Be2 b6 15. O-O Bb7 16. Rac1 Na5 17. Qb2 Rac8 18. h3 c5 19. dxc5 Rxc5 20. Rxc5 Qxc5 21. Rc1 Qe7 22. Nd4 Qg5 23. Bg4 Qd5 24. Bf3 Qd7 25. Bxb7 Nxb7 26. Nc6 Ra8 27. Qd4 Nc5 28. Qxd7 Nxd7 29. Rd1 Nc5 {White enjoys a small advantage, as his c6-knight is well placed and his majority can be proven more mobile than Black's queenside one.} 30. g4 $1 {The typical way of gaining more space.} g6 $6 {The text is weakening Black's kingside and especially the h6-pawn.} ({Preferable was} 30... Kf8 $14 {.}) 31. Kg2 Kg7 32. Rd2 $1 a6 (32... Ne4 $6 33. Rd7 $16 {fails to satisfy.}) 33. Rd6 $1 Rc8 34. Nd4 b5 $6 {Weakening the queenside cannot be recommended.} ({Preferable was} 34... Na4 35. h4 $14 {.}) 35. h4 $1 {With ideas as h5, targeting the h6-pawn.} b4 (35... a5 $6 36. Nxb5 Rb8 37. Nc3 Rb2 38. Rd5 {is again out of the question.}) 36. Rb6 a5 37. Rb5 Nd3 38. Rxa5 {White won a good pawn, but Black has obtained some counterplay.} Ne1+ 39. Kg3 Nc2 40. Nb3 $6 (40. Nf3 $1 {was clearer:} Rc3 41. Ne5 Kf6 {41...Ra3 42.Rxa3 bxa3 43.Nd3+-} 42. Kf4 g5+ 43. hxg5+ hxg5+ 44. Ke4 {.}) 40... Na3 41. Ra4 Rc4 42. Nd4 $1 Nc2 43. Nf3 Rc5 ({Or} 43... Rc3 44. Ne5 Kf6 45. Kf4 {.}) 44. Ra7 g5 (44... Na3 45. g5 h5 46. Nd4 {wouldn't have changed the outcome.}) 45. h5 Kg8 46. Nd2 Na3 47. Ne4 Rc2 (47... Rc6 {is not an improvement:} 48. Ra4 Rb6 49. Nc5 {.}) 48. Rb7 Rxa2 49. Rxb4 Rc2 50. Rb6 $1 Kh7 (50... Kg7 {loses to} 51. Nd6 {.}) 51. Rb7 $1 ({The mistaken} 51. Nd6 $2 {would save Black after} Nc4 52. Nxc4 {52.Rc6 Nxe3=} Rxc4 {.}) 51... Kg8 52. Nd6 Rc6 53. Nxf7 Nc4 54. Rd7 (54. Nxh6+ Rxh6 55. Rb5 {was an alternative win!}) 54... Rf6 55. Rd4 $1 Z0 ({Black resigned, as he has already lost too much material:} 55... Nxe3 56. Nxh6+ Rxh6 57. fxe3 {.}) 1-0

