{In this queenless middlegame, what is White's best move to capitalize on their position?} 23. g4 {[%mdl 32768]} ({Not helpful is} 23. Nb3 $6 Ne6 24. Rd7 Red8 25. Rb7 Rdb8) ({But maybe White could also try} 23. Nb5 Rad8 24. Nc7 Rxd1 25. Rxd1 Rc8 26. Nd5 $14 {. The text is logical; White gains space on the kingside. As this is still a queenless middlegame White seems to have better prospects anyway. His pieces are well placed and he can mobilise his kingside pawn majority more effectively than Black can do with his own queenside pawn majority.}) *

