1. d4 {[%mdl 32768]} Nf6 2. c4 e5 3. dxe5 Ne4 4. Nd2 Bb4 5. a3 Bxd2+ 6. Bxd2 Nc6 7. Nf3 Nxd2 8. Qxd2 Qe7 9. Qc3 O-O 10. Rd1 Re8 11. Rd5 b6 12. e3 Bb7 13. Be2 Rad8 14. O-O Nb8 15. Rd2 Bxf3 16. Bxf3 Qxe5 17. Qxe5 Rxe5 18. Rfd1 d6 19. b4 a5 20. Rd5 Rxd5 21. cxd5 Na6 22. Be2 Ra8 23. Bxa6 Rxa6 24. b5 Ra7 25. a4 Kf8 26. Rc1 Ke8 27. f4 {White advantage is small but permanent. His e-pawn is no match for the opponent c-pawn, so he has a mobile central majority, which could tell in the end.} Kd7 28. e4 Ra8 29. Kf2 Re8 30. Kf3 f6 31. h4 $1 ({The expansion on the kingside should be made carefully and obviously not by} 31. g4 $6 g5 32. h4 gxf4 33. Kxf4 Re5 34. g5 fxg5+ 35. hxg5 h6 {.}) 31... h5 $1 (31... h6 $6 32. h5 Rg8 33. Kg4 Re8 {( 33...g6 34.hxg6 Rxg6+ 35.Kf3 h5 36.Rh1 Rh6 37.Kf2 Ke7 38.Rh4 Kf7 39.g4 Kg6 40.f5+ Kg5 41.Kg3 hxg4 42.Rxg4+ Kh5 43.Kh3+- )} 34. Kf5 $16) ({Or} 31... Re7 $6 32. Rg1 h6 33. h5 Ke8 34. Re1 Kf7 35. Kg4 g6 36. hxg6+ Kxg6 37. Kf3 h5 38. Rh1 Rg7 39. Rh3 Rh7 40. Rg3+ Kf7 41. Ke3 Rh8 42. Kd4 Rh7 43. Rh3 Kg8 44. e5 $1 fxe5+ 45. fxe5 dxe5+ 46. Kxe5 Kf7 47. d6 $1 cxd6+ 48. Kxd6 $16 {, are clearly worst cases...}) 32. Rg1 Ke7 33. g4 hxg4+ 34. Rxg4 $6 (34. Kxg4 $1 {, was a better try:} Rh8 35. Rh1 Rh6 36. Kf5 $14 {.}) 34... Kf7 35. Rg2 Re7 $2 (35... g6 {, was a must.}) 36. h5 $1 Re8 37. Rc2 Re7 38. Rc4 $2 ({It is too early for} 38. f5 Kg8 39. Rg2 Kh7 40. Rg6 Rf7 41. Kg4 {( 41.h6 gxh6 42.Kg4 Rg7= )} Re7 42. h6 Rxe4+ 43. Kh5 gxh6 44. Rxf6 Kg7 45. Rxh6 Re5 46. Kg5 Rxd5 {.}) ({But after} 38. Rc6 $1 g6 39. h6 Kg8 40. e5 {, White would win!}) 38... Kg8 $2 ({After} 38... g6 $1 39. hxg6+ Kxg6 {, Black should be ample to keep the draw in hand as White can find no way to penetrate with his king:} 40. f5+ {( 40.Rc1 f5 41.exf5+ Kxf5 42.Rh1 Kg6= ) ( 40.Kg4 f5+= )} Kf7 41. Rc1 Ke8 42. Rh1 Rg7 43. Rh8+ Ke7 44. Rc8 Kd7 45. Rf8 Ke7 46. Rh8 Kd7 {.}) 39. Kg4 Kf7 40. Kf5 {Now Black is in trouble...} Rd7 41. Rc2 Re7 42. Rg2 $1 Re8 {Note that this was a 5-minute blitz game...} 43. h6 $2 ({White returns the favour. He could achieve a tremendous advantage with} 43. Rg1 $1 Rh8 {( 43...Re7 44.Rg6+- )} 44. Rc1 $1 Rxh5+ 45. Kg4 {.}) 43... g5 $6 ({Black panicked and by thinking that he was lost, blunders. He could still fight with} 43... gxh6 44. Rg6 Rxe4 $1 45. Rxf6+ Kg7 46. Rg6+ Kf7 47. Rxh6 Rc4 {, although White is still in the top after} 48. Rh7+ Ke8 49. Kg5 Rxa4 50. Rxc7 Rd4 51. f5 Rxd5 52. Kg6 {.}) 44. fxg5 (44. fxg5 {And Black resigned:} fxg5 45. Rxg5 Re5+ 46. Kf4 {.}) 1-0

