1. Z0 {A fixed pawn structure position, is one where multiple adjacent pawns cannot move, primarily because an opponent pawn (s) is directly in front (H.Kmoch) . Another terminology is: pawn set-ups where there is little or no possible mobility. Since there will be little pawn play, strategies are easier to determine. As it has been analysed in detail in the previous chapters, the main weapon here is the so-called minority attack. The defensive/counterplay set-ups are quite a few and we will examine them all in detail.} *

