1. d4 {[%mdl 32768]} Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nc3 d5 4. Bg5 Nbd7 5. e3 Be7 6. Nf3 O-O 7. Rc1 a6 8. cxd5 exd5 9. Bd3 c6 10. Qc2 Re8 11. O-O Nf8 12. h3 g6 13. Ne5 N6d7 14. Bf4 Nxe5 15. Bxe5 Bd6 16. Bxd6 Qxd6 17. Na4 Ne6 18. Nc5 Nxc5 19. Qxc5 Qf6 {A significant number of pieces have been exchanged already and another one is about to (...Bf5). Black’s position has no obvious weaknesses, which make White's task to prove an advantage rather difficult, if not possible at all… There is nothing else here to think about than the minority attack.} 20. b4 Bf5 {Exchanging the light squared bishops....} 21. Bxf5 Qxf5 22. a4 {White is ready for b5, creating a weakness in Black’s camp (a backward pawn on c6 or isolated pawns) and start pressuring it.} g5 $6 {Creates a new weakness without any valid reason; Black's kingside initiative is not serious.} ({Good defence is made via the third rank, so Black here should opt for} 22... Re6 $1 23. b5 axb5 24. axb5 Rf6 25. bxc6 bxc6 26. Rc2 $14 {and 'suffer'!}) 23. Qb6 Re7 $6 ({Another inaccuracy. Black had to opt for} 23... Qd7 24. b5 axb5 25. axb5 Re6 26. bxc6 bxc6 $14 {.}) 24. b5 axb5 25. axb5 cxb5 {Forced. Now Black has too many weaknesses to hold on.} 26. Rc5 $1 Kg7 27. Qxb5 Rd8 28. Qa5 (28. Qb1 $1 Qxb1 {( 28...Qe6?! 29.Rb5 Rdd7 30.Rb6+- )} 29. Rxb1 h5 30. Rcb5 Rdd7 31. Ra1 $16 {was also strong.}) 28... Red7 29. Rfc1 $2 {A bit naive.} ({Stronger was} 29. Rb5 Rc8 30. Qa2 $16 {.}) 29... g4 $1 30. hxg4 Qxg4 31. Rb5 Kh8 $2 {Losing an important tempo.} (31... Rd6 $1 {would give Black some good counterplay. The variations are many and White shouldn't be in danger to lose, if careful of course!}) 32. Qb6 $2 {Returning the favour!} ({After} 32. g3 $16 {, Black would be in a difficult position.}) 32... Rd6 $1 33. Qc7 Rg8 34. g3 Qe6 $6 {The position is a quite difficult one to be handled with accuracy.} ({Here Black missed the strong} 34... Rf6 $1 35. Qe5 {( 35.Rb6 Rf5 36.Rh6 Qf3 $13 )} Qf3 36. Rb2 h5 37. e4 $1 Kh7 38. Rc3 Qxc3 39. Qxf6 Qxb2 40. Qxf7+ {.}) 35. Re1 b6 36. e4 $1 dxe4 37. Rxe4 Qf6 $6 {But this was simply not the best.} ({Black had to opt for the natural} 37... Qxe4 38. Qxd6 Qe1+ 39. Kg2 Qe4+ 40. Kh2 Qf3 {, when he would be able to hold.}) 38. d5 h5 39. Kg2 $6 (39. Qc4 Rg5 40. Rf4 Qg6 41. Qb3 $14 {.}) 39... Qg6 $2 (39... h4 {would be unclear; all results would be possible.}) 40. Rf4 $6 (40. Re5 $1 {was quite strong:} Kh7 {( 40...h4 41.Rb4+- )} 41. Qe7 Rg7 42. Qh4 f5 {( 42...Kh6 43.Qf4+ Kh7 44.Rb4+- )} 43. Rb4 Qg5 44. Qh1 {.}) 40... Rg7 $2 (40... Rf8 {was a must:} 41. Qe7 Kg8 42. Kh2 $16 {.}) 41. Rh4 (41. Qe7 $1 Kh7 42. Qe5 {.}) 41... Rh7 42. Rbb4 $1 Qf6 43. Rhf4 Qd8 44. Qc3+ Kg8 {Black has created too many weaknesses around his king and it is not a surprise that he is simply lost...} 45. Rbc4 $1 Qf8 46. Rc8 Rd8 47. Rfc4 $1 Rh6 48. Rxd8 Qxd8 49. Rc8 1-0

