1. d4 {[%mdl 32768]} d5 2. c4 e6 3. Nc3 Nf6 4. Bg5 Nbd7 5. e3 c6 6. cxd5 exd5 7. Bd3 Be7 8. Qc2 O-O 9. Nf3 Re8 10. O-O Nf8 11. Ne5 Ng4 12. Bxe7 Qxe7 13. Nxg4 Bxg4 14. Ne2 Rad8 15. Ng3 g6 16. Rfe1 Bc8 17. Rac1 Ne6 18. Nf1 Rd6 19. Nd2 Ng7 20. Qa4 a6 21. Qa3 Qd8 22. b4 {After some manoeuvres, White opts for the usual plan...} g5 ({Black decides to get active on the kingside but he could also play} 22... Bf5 23. Bxf5 Nxf5 24. Qd3 Rde6 25. a4 Nd6 {, with a great game.}) 23. Qc3 f5 $6 {The text is not really in need.} ({Black should opt for} 23... g4 24. a4 Bf5 $13 {.}) 24. a4 Rh6 25. b5 axb5 26. axb5 Qf6 27. bxc6 bxc6 {White has concluded his plan and he has the advantage. Black is still looking for his chances.} 28. Ra1 $6 (28. Nf3 $1 {should be quite pleasant for White:} g4 29. Ne5 Qh4 30. h3 $1 gxh3 31. g3 $16 {.}) 28... Rf8 29. Ra8 $6 ({The advantage should be preserved by the prophylactic} 29. Ra2 $1 {.}) 29... f4 $1 30. exf4 ({White should think of} 30. e4 g4 $1 {30...f3? 31.g3+-} 31. Nf1 Qh4 $13 {.}) 30... Qxf4 31. Nf3 g4 32. Qd2 $1 {A saving resource...} Qf6 $2 ({Black is even trying to win! He should opt for the natural} 32... Qxd2 33. Nxd2 Bf5 34. Rxf8+ Kxf8 {.}) 33. Ng5 (33. Ne5 $1 Qh4 34. h3 $16 {was natural and good.}) 33... Bf5 ({Or} 33... Rg6 34. Bxg6 {34.h4!? h6 35.Qc2 $16} Qxg6 35. h4 h6 36. Re5 $16 {.}) 34. Rxf8+ Kxf8 35. Bxf5 $2 ({It was time for White to benefit from Black's decisions (23...f5 and 32...Qf6), which created weaknesses around his king, with} 35. Qf4 $1 Kg8 {35...Bxd3?! 36.Qb8++-} 36. Bxf5 Nxf5 37. Re8+ Kg7 38. Qc7+ Kg6 39. Rg8+ Kh5 40. Nxh7 {.}) 35... Qxf5 36. f3 ({Also good was} 36. Nf7 $1 Re6 37. Ne5 Kg8 38. Qa5 $16 {.}) 36... Rg6 $2 {Black continues to play with ghosts!} ({He should have opted for} 36... gxf3 37. Nxf3 Rf6 38. Ne5 $16 {.}) 37. Re5 $6 ({Again, White misses his chance:} 37. Qb4+ $1 Kg8 38. Re5 Qf8 39. Qxf8+ Kxf8 40. Nxh7+ Kg8 41. Ng5 {.}) 37... Qb1+ 38. Kf2 $2 {But this is too much.} ({After} 38. Re1 $1 Qf5 {, White can play the winning} 39. Qb4+ {.}) 38... Rf6 $1 {Back to business!} 39. Re1 Qf5 40. Re5 (40. Ra1 Kg8 41. Ra8+ Rf8 42. Rxf8+ Qxf8 {.}) 40... Qb1 41. Qa5 {A last winning attempt.} Kg8 $1 42. Qa8+ Rf8 43. Qxc6 Qb2+ {White cannot avoid the perpetual check: 44.Kg3!?  44.Kf1 Qb1+ 44...Nh5+ 45.Kh4 Nf4 46.Nxh7! Nxg2+ 47.Kh5 Nf4+ 48.Kg5 Kxh7 49.Re7+ Kg8 50.Qh6 Nh3+ 51.Kh5 Nf4+= .} 1/2-1/2

