16. Qxb6 {[%csl Gb6,Rb7][%mdl 32768] Black still appears to be in trouble - the white queen is very well placed on b6, trying the c8-bishop down to the defence of the b7-pawn.} Rb8 {[%csl Gb7][%cal Gc8f5,Gf5g4] Black now has the bishop pair and attacking chances on the kingside. By comparison, White is too late with his plan, the minority attack.} *

