18. h4 $2 {[%mdl 32768]} Qe7 19. Ne2 Bg4 20. Nf4 g5 $1 21. hxg5 Qxg5 {[%csl Rf4][%cal Gh5h4,Gf8d6] White 'refused' to adopt the standard minority attack plan on the queenside and has therefore failed to react to Black's kingside initiative. His position is inferior and under fire from Black's pieces. This is a good example of punishment for the side that doesn't achieve any plans, a concept of great significance in modern chess.} *

