{What move should White play to execute their queenside strategy, considering their more active bishop and the fixed central structure?} 24. b4 $1 {[%mdl 32768]} g5 {A natural reaction. Black's main counterplay lies in the ...f4 advance, which will weaken the d4-pawn, turning it to a target.} 25. Qd2 $1 {No hurry! White keeps this advance (...f4) in reserve.} *

