[SourceTitle "https://www.chessable.co"]

{A simple and effective plan if it can be applied. The concept is simple: after White's b4-b5 advance, which will weaken the c4-square, Black will exchange the light-squared bishops and then occupy the c4-square with a knight, usually via b6 or d6. Although this looks like a ‘great’ plan, it has two minuses; first it loses valuable time and second it doesn’t create any activity against White’s plans.} 1. Z0 *

[Event "The Strategy Instructors Volume 1: Pawn "]
[Site "?"]
[Date "2024.05.28"]
[Round "?"]
[White "5.3) Light-squared Bishops' E"]
[Black "Trifunovic, Petar vs. Pirc"]
[Result "*"]
[SetUp "1"]
