[EventDate "2024.??.??"]
[SourceTitle "https://www.chessable.co"]

{With so many of Black's pawns being on light squares, the c8-bishop could become a bad piece. Can you find a way to exchange it?} 12... g6 {[%cal Gf8e6,Ge6g7,Gc8f5][%mdl 32768] This idea was first introduced in 1930 by Fritz Saemisch. Black's plan is simple: ...Ne6-g7 and ...Bf5, exchanging light-squared bishops.} *

