1. d4 {[%mdl 32768]} Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nf3 d5 4. Nc3 Be7 5. Bg5 O-O 6. e3 Nbd7 7. Rc1 a6 8. cxd5 exd5 9. Bd3 Re8 10. O-O c6 11. Qc2 Nf8 12. a3 g6 13. Na4 Ne6 14. Bh4 Ng7 15. Nc5 Rb8 $6 ({Everything is new when it is well forgotten! It is essential for the black side to proceed with pieces’ exchanges, so} 15... Nd7 $1 {still seems to be best.}) 16. b4 Bf5 17. Ne5 Bxd3 18. Qxd3 Ne4 $6 ({Black could think of} 18... Ng4 $5 19. Bxe7 {19.Nxg4 Bxh4 20.Nh6+ Kf8 21.f4 f5 22.e4 dxe4 23.Qc4 Qd5 24.Qxd5 cxd5 25.Nd7+ Ke7 26.Nxb8 Ne6= $13} Nxe5 20. dxe5 Qxe7 21. f4 Ne6 22. Nb3 $14 {,}) ({but not} 18... Nf5 $2 19. Bxf6 Bxf6 20. Ned7 Ra8 21. Nxf6+ Qxf6 22. Nxb7 {.}) 19. Bxe7 $6 ({The text seems logical, but Black missed a good chance:} 19. Nxb7 $1 Rxb7 20. Nxc6 Qa8 21. Nxe7+ Rexe7 22. Bxe7 Rxe7 23. Qc2 $16 {.}) 19... Qxe7 20. Nxe4 ({Now the 'combination' of the previous move is not that effective:} 20. Nxa6 bxa6 21. Nxc6 Qb7 22. Nxb8 Rxb8 23. Rc2 Nd6 24. Rfc1 Ne6 $13 {. White was forced on the text move, as Black was planning ...Nd6 and ...f6, with a perfect position.}) 20... dxe4 21. Qb3 (21. Qxe4 $2 f6 $1 {would be childish.}) 21... Ne6 {An also typical pawn structure transformation occurred. Although it is still possible to continue with the minority attack (a4, b5), there is a second, quite active continuation.} 22. f4 $5 exf3 (22... f6 $6 23. Nc4 f5 24. a4 {favours White.}) 23. Rxf3 Ng5 $6 ({Correct was} 23... f6 $1 24. Nd3 Rbd8 25. Rcf1 f5 $13 {.}) 24. Rf2 Qe6 25. Qxe6 Rxe6 26. h4 $1 Ne4 27. Rf4 (27. Rxf7 $2 Rxe5 {.}) 27... Ng3 28. Kf2 Nh5 29. Rf3 f5 30. g4 $1 fxg4 (30... Rxe5 $6 {looks very attractive, but White can come out on the top:} 31. gxh5 $1 {31.dxe5? fxg4 32.Rf4 Nxf4 33.exf4 Rd8 $17} Re4 32. hxg6 hxg6 33. Rg1 Kg7 34. Rfg3 {34.h5?! Rg4=} Rxh4 35. Rxg6+ Kf7 36. Rg7+ Ke6 37. Ke2 $16 {.}) 31. Nxg4 Re4 32. Rg1 Kg7 (32... Rd8 $5 33. Nh6+ Kg7 34. Nf7 Rb8 35. Nd6 Re6 36. Nf5+ Kg8 37. Ng3 $14 {.}) 33. Ke2 Rbe8 $6 ({Better was} 33... Rf8 34. Rxf8 Kxf8 35. Kd3 Re6 36. Rf1+ Ke7 37. a4 $14 {.}) 34. Kd3 R8e7 35. a4 $1 {It is never too late for the minority attack! White's advantage is growing.} a5 {So, Black tries to be active.} 36. bxa5 c5 37. Ne5 $1 Rxh4 38. Rgf1 cxd4 39. exd4 Re8 40. Rf7+ Kh6 41. Rxb7 Nf4+ 42. Kc4 Rc8+ 43. Kb5 Ne6 44. Rff7 $1 Nxd4+ 45. Kb6 Re4 (45... Kg5 46. a6 $1 Re4 47. Rfe7 {.}) 46. Rbe7 Nf5 47. Rxh7+ Kg5 48. Nf7+ Kf4 49. Rh4+ $1 Nxh4 50. Rxe4+ {Black resigned as White's a-pawn is too quick: 50...Kxe4 50...Kg3 51.a6+- 51.Nd6+ Kd5 52.Nxc8+- .} 1-0

