1. Z0 {A very common plan. Black can physically prevent White's b4-b5 advance with ...b5. The resulting weakness on c6 can be ‘easily’ covered by placing a knight on c4 (...Nc4) via b6 or d6. Well, Black must ensure to have this knight placed on c4, otherwise his backward c-pawn will come under heavy attack. Usually, White tries to break down Black's pawn structure with a central e4 strike.} *

