{This is another often used concept; Black may reply to White's b4-b5 with ...c5, ignoring the resulting isolated pawn on d5 and creating a powerful initiative in the center. In practice, this plan has proved to be one of the most dangerous for the side executing the minority attack, as it contains a lot of 'energy' that is seeded in the center.} 1. Z0 *

