1. d4 {[%mdl 32768]} d5 2. Nf3 Nf6 3. c4 e6 4. Nc3 c6 5. cxd5 exd5 6. Qc2 g6 7. Bg5 Bg7 8. e3 Bf5 9. Bd3 Bxd3 10. Qxd3 Nbd7 11. O-O O-O 12. Rab1 Qe7 13. Rfc1 Qe6 14. Nd2 Rfe8 15. Bxf6 Bxf6 16. b4 Rac8 17. b5 $6 ({Too optimistic. White should have opted for} 17. Na4 Qd6 18. Nc5 Rc7 $13 {.}) 17... c5 $1 18. dxc5 ({And now he should also seriously consider} 18. Nf3 c4 19. Qc2 Bd8 $15 {.}) 18... Nxc5 19. Qf1 d4 20. exd4 Bxd4 {Black got rid of his central pawns, offering to his bishop a wide range of action and he can already state that he has gained a nice advantage.} 21. Re1 Qf5 22. Ne2 Bf6 23. Nc4 Ne4 24. Ng3 Nxg3 25. Rxe8+ Rxe8 26. hxg3 Bd4 27. Rd1 Qc5 28. Na5 Rd8 29. Rd2 Qc7 30. Nb3 Bb6 31. Rxd8+ Qxd8 32. Qe2 Qd5 {Black still holds a nice advantage but in the end he couldn't achieve more than the split of the point. The rest of the game is irrelevant to our subject.} 33. g4 h6 34. Kf1 Kg7 35. Qb2+ Kh7 36. Qe2 a5 37. bxa6 bxa6 38. Kg1 a5 39. Nc1 a4 40. Nd3 Qc4 41. Kf1 a3 42. g3 Bd4 43. Nf4 Qc1+ 44. Kg2 Qb2 45. Kf1 Kg7 46. Nd3 Qb7 47. Kg1 g5 48. Kh2 Qc6 49. Nb4 Qc5 50. Nd3 Qc6 51. Nb4 Qb6 52. Nd3 Qb7 53. Kg1 Qb1+ 54. Kg2 Bc3 55. Nc5 Qb4 56. Ne4 Bb2 57. Qd3 Qb7 58. f3 Qc6 59. Nd6 Kg8 60. Nf5 Qe6 1/2-1/2

