{Well, Black will not always be as successful as in the previous example. White can usually drag out a slight advantage but of course, Black is still very much in the game and can present a very tough fight.} 1. d4 {[%mdl 32768]} d5 2. c4 e6 3. Nc3 Nf6 4. cxd5 exd5 5. Bg5 Be7 6. e3 O-O 7. Bd3 Re8 8. Qc2 Nbd7 9. Nf3 c6 10. h3 Nf8 11. Bf4 Bd6 12. Bxd6 Qxd6 13. O-O Qe7 14. Rab1 Ne4 15. b4 Bf5 16. Rb3 {White seems to be in the right track, but Black is not left without positive ideas...} Rad8 $2 (16... Rac8 $1 {looked more to the point:} 17. b5 c5 $1 18. dxc5 {18.Nxd5? Qd8! 19.Nf4 c4 20.Bxc4 Nd6 $17} Rxc5 {18...Qxc5 19.Nd4 Ne6 20.Nxf5 Nxc3 21.Nd6 Qxd6 22.Rxc3 Rxc3 23.Qxc3 d4 24.exd4 Nxd4=} 19. Qb2 Ne6 $13 {.}) 17. b5 c5 ({Black had no choice. After} 17... cxb5 18. Rxb5 Nxc3 19. Qxc3 Bxd3 20. Qxd3 b6 21. a4 $16 {, another minority attack will be seen against b6.}) 18. dxc5 Qxc5 19. Nd4 Bg6 ({What else? If} 19... Rc8 {, then} 20. Rc1 Bg6 21. Nxe4 Qxc2 22. Rxc2 dxe4 23. Rxc8 Rxc8 24. Be2 $1 {24.Bf1 Nd7 25.Ra3 $14} Nd7 25. Ra3 Ra8 26. h4 $16 {.}) 20. Nxe4 $1 Qxc2 21. Bxc2 Bxe4 ({Black's problems could not be solved either with the alternative} 21... dxe4 22. Ra3 Ra8 23. Bb3 $16 {.}) 22. Bxe4 Rxe4 ({Or} 22... dxe4 23. Ra3 Ra8 24. Rc1 a6 25. bxa6 Rxa6 26. Rxa6 bxa6 27. Rc6 Ra8 28. Nf5 $16 {.}) 23. Ra3 Ne6 $5 {An interesting pawn sacrifice in exchange for some activity.} ({Black would be tied down after the prosaic} 23... Ra8 24. Rc1 Re7 25. b6 {25.Rc5 Rd7 26.Rac3 $16} a6 26. Rac3 $16 {.}) 24. Nxe6 ({White could also consider} 24. f3 $5 Re5 25. Rxa7 Nxd4 26. exd4 Re7 27. Rc1 $16 {,}) ({or} 24. Rxa7 Nxd4 25. exd4 Rb8 26. Rd1 $16 {.}) 24... fxe6 25. Rxa7 Rd7 26. Rc1 $2 ({The accurate} 26. Rb1 $1 {should be proved enough:} e5 27. a4 d4 28. a5 $1 dxe3 29. fxe3 Rd2 30. Rxb7 Rxe3 31. Rb8+ Kf7 32. Rf1+ Kg6 33. Rf3 {.}) 26... Rb4 $1 27. a4 e5 $1 {Now Black has good counterplay due to his potential passed d-pawn.} 28. Rc6 $6 ({White's best chances lay in} 28. Rc8+ Kf7 29. Rb8 Kf6 30. Raxb7 Rxb7 31. Rxb7 Rxa4 32. Rb6+ Ke7 33. Kf1 $16 {.}) 28... d4 $1 29. exd4 exd4 30. b6 bxc6 (30... d3 {was good enough for the draw:} 31. Rc7 {31.Rc8+? Kf7 32.Rc7 32.Rc1 d2 33.Rd1 Re4 34.Kf1 Rde7-+ 32...Ke6 32...Rbd4? 33.Raxb7+- 33.Raxb7 Rb1+ 34.Kh2 Rd6-+} Rd8 32. Raxb7 d2 33. Rxg7+ {.}) 31. Rxd7 Rxb6 32. Rxd4 c5 33. Re4 Rb4 34. f3 c4 35. a5 Ra4 1/2-1/2

