1. c4 {[%mdl 32768]} e6 2. Nc3 d5 3. d4 Nf6 4. cxd5 exd5 5. Bg5 Be7 6. e3 O-O 7. Bd3 Nbd7 8. Nf3 Re8 9. O-O c6 10. Qc2 Nf8 11. h3 g6 12. Bxf6 Bxf6 13. b4 Ne6 14. Rfd1 ({Probably it is too early for} 14. b5 $6 c5 $1 15. dxc5 Nxc5 16. Rac1 Be6 {, when Black would be rather active.}) 14... a6 15. Rab1 Be7 (15... Ng5 16. Nxg5 Bxg5 17. a4 Be6 {, is an alternative continuation.}) 16. a4 Bd6 {A typical rearrangement of the darksquared bishop, aiming to reinforce the attack towards the white king.} 17. Re1 ({White could play the main theme in this pawn structure:} 17. b5 axb5 18. axb5 Ng5 19. Nxg5 Qxg5 20. bxc6 bxc6 {( 20...Bxh3? 21.f4 Qg3 22.cxb7 Qxe3+ 23.Qf2+- ) (Or 20...Rb8? 21.f4 Qg3 22.Nxd5+- )} 21. Kf1 $13 {. And probably, this was a better try, than the one chosen in the game…}) 17... Ng5 18. Nxg5 Qxg5 19. Kf1 Be6 20. Ne2 ({Only Black would be happy now after the thematical} 20. b5 $6 axb5 21. axb5 c5 22. dxc5 Bxc5 $17 {.}) 20... Qh4 21. Ng1 Qe7 22. Qc3 Qf6 23. Qc2 ({Of course, not} 23. Nf3 $2 Bxh3 {.}) 23... Rac8 24. Qd1 Kg7 25. Rb2 Qe7 26. Qb1 Qf6 27. Qd1 {Black has an easy game and rightly he decided to continue the game.} h5 $1 28. Qf3 Qg5 29. Qd1 Bd7 30. b5 $6 ({White should go after a 'waiting policy' with something like} 30. Nf3 Qe7 31. Qb3 {.}) 30... cxb5 $1 ({Also good was} 30... axb5 31. axb5 c5 32. dxc5 Bxc5 33. Nf3 Qf6 34. Rb1 g5 $17 {.}) 31. axb5 a5 {Black's position is rather attractive. He can try to benefit from his bishop pair and his passed a-pawn. On the other hand, weaknesses like his isolated d-pawn are not counting as White is not in a position to even approach it!} 32. Rc2 Qf6 33. Rxc8 Rxc8 34. Re2 Qd8 (34... Bf5 $5 35. Bxf5 Qxf5 36. Ra2 Bb4 $17 {.}) 35. Rb2 (35. Rc2 {, doesn't hold:} a4 36. Ne2 {( 36.Rxc8 Qxc8 37.Qxa4? Qc1+ 38.Ke2 Qxg1-+ )} a3 {( 36...Rxc2 37.Qxc2 Qa5 38.Nc3 a3 $17 )} 37. Ra2 Qa5 {.}) 35... a4 36. Ne2 Qa5 37. Rb1 ({There is no difference with} 37. Qe1 {, as Black's passed pawn is too strong:} Qa8 {( 37...Qxe1+ 38.Kxe1 a3 $17 )} 38. Rb1 a3 {.}) 37... Bb4 (37... a3 {, was more accurate.}) 38. Kg1 Bxb5 39. Bxb5 Qxb5 {Black even won material and the end is near.} 40. Nf4 a3 $1 (40... Rc4 41. Qf3 a3 $17 {, wasn't that clear.}) 41. Nd3 (41. Qb3 Qc4 $1 42. Qxb4 Qxb4 43. Rxb4 a2 44. Ra4 Rc1+ 45. Kh2 a1=Q 46. Rxa1 Rxa1 47. Nxd5 b5 {.}) 41... Rc4 42. Ne5 ({After} 42. Qb3 {, Black can prevail by} Rc3 $1 43. Qxb4 {( 43.Qxc3 Bxc3 44.Rxb5 a2-+ )} Qxd3 44. Ra1 Rb3 45. Qd6 Rb1+ 46. Rxb1 Qxb1+ 47. Kh2 a2 48. Qe5+ Kh7 49. Qxd5 Kg8 50. Qd8+ Kg7 {.}) 42... Rc3 $1 (42... Rc3 {White resigned as he had no satisfactory continuation at his disposal:} 43. g4 {( 43.Qf3 f6-+ )} hxg4 44. Qxg4 a2 45. Ra1 Bd6 {.}) 0-1

