1. c4 {[%mdl 32768]} e6 2. Nc3 d5 3. d4 Bb4 4. cxd5 exd5 5. Bf4 c6 6. e3 Bf5 7. Nge2 Ne7 8. Qb3 Qb6 9. a3 Ba5 10. Qa2 Qd8 11. b4 Bb6 12. Ng3 Be6 13. Bd3 Ng6 14. Nce2 Nd7 15. O-O O-O 16. Rac1 Re8 17. Qb2 a6 18. a4 Nf6 19. b5 $6 ({Inaccurate. White should have opted for} 19. Bg5 $1 Bc7 20. b5 $14 {.}) 19... cxb5 $6 ({Quite optimistic. After} 19... axb5 20. axb5 Nxf4 21. Nxf4 Bd7 22. Bf5 Bc7 23. Bxd7 Qxd7 24. Nd3 Bd6 {, Black should be OK.}) 20. axb5 (20. Bg5 $1 {looks nice for White:} bxa4 21. Nc3 Ba5 22. Nxa4 $13 {.}) 20... a5 ({Black should go for} 20... Nxf4 21. Nxf4 a5 $13 {.}) 21. Bg5 $1 h6 22. Bxf6 Qxf6 23. Bxg6 $6 {Surrendering all bishops cannot be a good strategy.} ({Natural was} 23. Nc3 Nh4 24. Rfd1 $14 {.}) 23... fxg6 $1 24. Nf4 Bf7 {Black has got the bishop pair and a good passed a-pawn; he should feel quite comfortable...} 25. Nd3 h5 26. Ne2 h4 27. Ne5 g5 $2 {This allows White to become active.} ({Correct was} 27... h3 28. gxh3 Be6 $13 {.}) 28. f4 $1 Be6 29. Nc3 $2 (29. h3 $1 Bf5 30. Nc3 Rad8 31. Na4 $16 {should be great for White.}) 29... a4 $1 30. Qa2 gxf4 31. Rxf4 $2 {A blunder.} ({Forced was} 31. Ne2 $1 Ba7 32. Rc3 Bb8 $13 {.}) 31... Qxe5 $1 32. dxe5 Bxe3+ 33. Kh1 d4 $1 34. Nd5 Bxf4 {Black won material and with bishop pair and his passed pawn, he should prevail.} 35. Rc7 Bxe5 36. Rxb7 Rad8 37. Re7 Rf8 $1 38. Qb1 Bxd5 39. Rxe5 h3 40. Kg1 hxg2 41. Rxd5 Rxd5 42. Qa2 Rfd8 43. b6 Kh8 $2 {The queen can be a quite tricky piece, especially in quicker time controls and here is of no exception.} ({The winning} 43... d3 44. Qd2 R5d7 {wasn’t that difficult.}) 44. b7 Rb5 45. Qf2 $1 Kg8 46. Qh4 Rb8 47. Qxd4 R5xb7 48. Qxa4 Rf7 49. Kxg2 {Now the position is drawish, but the game was of a limited time control, with a few mistakes to follow. In the end Black prevailed.} Rf6 50. Qc4+ Kh8 51. Qh4+ Rh6 52. Qd4 Rf8 53. h4 $2 {The decisive mistake.} Rg6+ 54. Kh2 Rgf6 55. Kg3 Rg6+ 56. Kh2 Re8 57. Qc4 Rge6 58. Qd5 Re5 59. Qf7 R8e7 60. Qf3 Re2+ 61. Kg1 R7e5 62. Qd3 R2e3 63. Qg6 R3e4 64. Qd6 Rh5 65. Kg2 Rhxh4 66. Kg3 Kh7 67. Qd5 Reg4+ 68. Kf3 Rf4+ 69. Ke3 Rf6 70. Qd7 Kh6 71. Qc8 Kh7 72. Qd7 Rh5 73. Qc7 Rhf5 74. Qh2+ Kg8 75. Qb8+ Rf8 76. Qb3+ Kh7 77. Qe6 Rf3+ 78. Ke2 Rf2+ 79. Ke1 R8f5 80. Qc8 g6 81. Qb7+ Rf7 82. Qh1+ Kg7 83. Qc6 R2f6 84. Qe8 g5 85. Ke2 Rf2+ 86. Ke1 R2f5 87. Qe4 Kh6 88. Qh1+ Kg6 89. Qc6+ Kg7 90. Qe4 Rf1+ 91. Ke2 R7f2+ 92. Kd3 Rf3+ 93. Ke2 R3f2+ 94. Kd3 Rf5 95. Ke2 R1f4 96. Qb7+ Kh6 97. Qh1+ Kg6 98. Qc6+ Kh5 99. Qh1+ Rh4 100. Qc6 Rh2+ 101. Ke3 Rf4 102. Qe6 Rhh4 103. Qd7 Rf6 104. Qh7+ Kg4 105. Qe4+ Rf4 106. Qg2+ Kh5 107. Qb7 Rh3+ 108. Ke2 Kh4 109. Qh7+ Kg3 110. Qd3+ Kh2 111. Qd6 Rg3 112. Qe5 Rff3 113. Qh8+ Kg2 114. Qa8 g4 115. Qe4 Kg1 116. Qb1+ Kh2 117. Qh7+ Rh3 118. Qc7+ Kg2 119. Qc6 {Finally Black made it and now he is quite near to his target.} Rh2 $1 120. Qc1 Kg3+ 0-1

